# Zepatrol Privacy Policy

**Last Updated**: October 17, 2025

## Summary

Zepatrol takes user privacy seriously. **We do not collect, store, or share any personal data.**

## Data Collection

### Data We Do NOT Collect ‚ùå
- Personal information (name, email, phone, etc.)
- Browsing history
- Visited URLs
- IP address
- Location data
- Usage statistics
- Analytics data
- Cookies

### Data Used by the Extension ‚úÖ

The extension stores **only on your device** (local storage) the following data:

1. **Whitelist**
   - List of protected crypto sites
   - Automatically updated from GitHub
   - Not sent to any servers

2. **Your Custom Sites**
   - Sites you add yourself
   - Stored only on your device
   - Never uploaded anywhere

3. **Settings**
   - Extension enabled/disabled status
   - Personalization preferences
   - Completely local

4. **Statistics**
   - Number of blocked attempts
   - Only numerical values
   - No information about which sites were blocked

All this data is stored **only on your device** using Chrome Storage API and **never leaves your device**.

## External Connections

The extension makes internet connections only in the following cases:

### GitHub API (Whitelist Updates)
- **When**: During initial setup and weekly automatic updates
- **Where**: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zepatrol/whitelist-db/main/`
- **What's sent**: Nothing (only file download)
- **What's received**: Updated whitelist (site list)

No personal data is sent during this process. Only a standard HTTP GET request is made.

## Permissions Explanation

The extension uses the following Chrome permissions:

### `storage`
- **Purpose**: Store whitelist and settings
- **Data**: Only on device, in Chrome Storage
- **Sharing**: Never shared anywhere

### `bookmarks`
- **Purpose**: Provide phishing protection through bookmark checking
- **Access**: Only reads bookmark URLs
- **Transmission**: Never sent anywhere

### `alarms`
- **Purpose**: Timer for weekly whitelist updates
- **Usage**: Only local timer

### `tabs`
- **Purpose**: Show blocked page
- **Access**: Only active tab URL
- **Usage**: For URL whitelist checking

### `webNavigation`
- **Purpose**: Detect navigation from bookmarks
- **Access**: Navigation events
- **Usage**: For bookmark detection

### `<all_urls>` (Host Permissions)
- **Purpose**: Perform phishing checks on all websites
- **Usage**: Only whitelisted sites are checked
- **Data collection**: No data is collected

## Third-Party Services

The extension **does not send data to any third-party services**:

- ‚ùå No Google Analytics
- ‚ùå No advertising networks
- ‚ùå No tracking services
- ‚ùå No error reporting services
- ‚ùå No social media widgets

Only external connection: GitHub (for whitelist updates)

## Children's Privacy

The extension does not knowingly collect data from children under 13. We **don't collect data from any users anyway**.

## Data Security

- All data is stored on your device (Chrome Storage)
- Compliant with Chrome's security standards
- No server-side data storage
- Encryption: Chrome's native storage encryption

## User Rights

### Delete Your Data
You can delete all data by removing the extension:
1. Open `chrome://extensions/`
2. Click "Remove" on Zepatrol
3. All local data is deleted

### Export Your Data
You can export your settings as JSON from the Settings page using the "Export" button.

## Changes

If this privacy policy is updated:
- Announced in extension update notes
- Published in GitHub repository changelog
- Users are notified

## Contact

For privacy-related questions:
- Email: privacy@zepatrol.xyz
- GitHub Issues: https://github.com/zepatrol/zepatrol/issues

## Legal Compliance

### GDPR (Europe)
Zepatrol is fully compliant with GDPR because it **does not process any personal data**.

### KVKK (Turkey)
Zepatrol is fully compliant with KVKK because it **does not collect any personal data**.

### CCPA (California)
Zepatrol is fully compliant with CCPA because it **does not sell user data** (doesn't collect any).

## Open Source

All source code is open on GitHub:
- https://github.com/zepatrol/zepatrol
- You can verify our privacy claims by examining the code

